DataElement.preferredDefinition: A sample or part of a thing, or of several things, taken to demonstrate or to determine the character of the whole, e.g. a substance, or portion of material obtained for use in testing, examination, or study; particularly, a preparation of tissue or bodily fluid taken for examination or diagnosis.:A rule which guides how an activity should be performed; a set of formal rules used to specify the format of an exchange of data._Having little (physical) length or seeming to be limited in (temporal) duration.:A general or descriptive designator for an object, work of art, or literary composition._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
